data.mission: Implement prototype numerical / symbolic experiments that illustrate the behavior or consequences of the most promising candidate framework(s). This may include: toy-model simulations, symbolic derivations (e.g., effective action, renormalization flow), entanglement structure diagnostics, or small-scale lattice/graph models demonstrating emergence of classicality from quantum rules. Produce reproducible code and example outputs (plots, tables).

Compose the final deliverable: a comprehensive technical report that documents the literature baseline, the candidate frameworks, results of prototype experiments, critical analysis of limitations, and a prioritized research roadmap (next 1-, 3-, and 5-year milestones). Include equations, figures, references (BibTeX), and appendices with code links and data artifacts.

Update spec to define 'benchmark contract' sections: required fields, allowed ranges, uncertainty reporting, and acceptance tests; implement contract checks in the validator and add at least one negative test case.
Generate docs from schema (or vice versa), enforce schema validation as a pre-commit/CI gate for all benchmark outputs, and deprecate any ad-hoc formats not represented in schema.json.

Define a 'green' checklist (CI passing, e2e runnable, one benchmark validated) and freeze new benchmark additions until the checklist is satisfied; track progress via a single milestone tied to v0.1.0.
